data.name: Sync_Version_Requires_Downgrade_Message
data.value:
Your SYNC Version is higher than supported by the 'reformat tool'.
FordSyncDownloader can automatically select the downgrade package.
Once you have downgraded your Sync version you can start over by selecting 'Any other SYNC Version' and choosing your desired new version.
Alternatively you can use 'Manual Configuration' mode which allows you to create simple update packages for individual packages e.g APPS.
Click Yes to automatically select the Downgrade package, otherwise click no if you plan to use Manual Configuration or know better!

data.name: label4.Text
data.value:
This section can be used to do manual "autoupdates" use this section only if you know what you are doing or if you are following some steps listed online by CyanLabs.
This section will not be supported unless associated with a CyanLabs guide.
The section can not be used to install MAPS due to missing licenses!
Select the IVSU's you wish to install and press "Start"

data.name: lblIssueDesc.Text
data.value: Something not going to plan? Click "Discord" or "Community Forum" to the left to get some support. If you have your USB drive selected we will automatically copy the contents of your SyncMyRide folder, autoinstall.lst and reformat.lst to your clipboard, simply paste this in a message and await a response.

data.name: Manual_Mode_Message
data.value:
You can use manual mode to semi-automatically create autoinstall.lst files for specific sections of the 'release'
A good example would be to upgrade only the APPS package from 20021 to 20136.
To use this function select a release and USB Drive and then click this button again.

data.name: Process_Complete_Message
data.value:
The download and copy of the files is now complete, simply eject this USB from your computer and insert it in your car, make sure the engine is running!
If you would like further instructions click Yes to open our online guide directly to the in car section.
If you used the 'DOWNGRADE' package, once the above steps are done return to this application to update to your desired version
